Renowned motorcyclist Gavin Ramsay died while racing this past weekend. CAPE TOWN - Killarney International Raceway management says an investigation will be conducted by Motorsport South Africa into a crash that claimed the life of a renowned motorcyclist.Gavin Ramsay died while racing this past weekend. Raceway executive manager Des Easom says a probe will be launched. An investigation will help to gather information and the correct facts on what occurred. That will be done by the Western Province Motor Club and the governing body that governs motor sports across South Africa. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)